messageBody:
--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, oliver langan <oliver@...> wrote:
>
> I think one of the benefits of QuickScript is its imprecision.
>

That's a pretty imprecise statment! Joke. I have to disagree. Learning
it and having to struggle with the crude hand written alphabet to make
fonts, and then having to overcome the inadequacy of the defnitions of
what each letter means, has made me yearn for a much more thorough,
better thought out manual.

Paul
